        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/{size}/326_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T01:00:58.540Z",
        "cooked": "<p>There is no password-based authentication option available.  The closest one way to hack this would be to set up your verify peers string to only accept one certificate from all servers and clients, and then have your certificate require a password. (see --tls_password in <a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/tls.html#configuring-tls\">Configuring TLS</a>).</p>\n<p>If you need the ability to match against other fields in the certificate, I\u2019d be happy to review a PR that adds additional field names to the TLS implementation. <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slightly_smiling_face.png?v=9\" title=\":slightly_smiling_face:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slightly_smiling_face:\"></p>",
